---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="shenas community -- write plugins, share what you build"
  description="The open-source community hub for shenas. Write source plugins, build dashboards, and help others understand their data."
>
  <!-- Nav -->
  <nav>
    <div class="nav-inner">
      <a href="/" class="nav-logo">shenas<span class="nav-org">.org</span></a>
      <div class="nav-links">
        <a href="#start">Get started</a>
        <a href="#source-plugin">Source plugins</a>
        <a href="#other-plugins">Other plugins</a>
        <a href="#share">Share</a>
        <a href="https://shenas.net">shenas.net</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/shenas-org/shenas">GitHub</a>
        <a href="https://discord.gg/mY74eRU7MV">Discord</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <header class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Write a plugin.<br /><span class="accent">Share what you build.</span></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        shenas is an open-source quantified-self platform. Source plugins
        bring data in, transforms shape it, dashboards make it visible.
        Every piece is a plugin you can write, share, and improve.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="#source-plugin" class="btn btn-primary">Write your first plugin</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/shenas-org/shenas" class="btn btn-secondary">Browse the code</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- Get started -->
  <section id="start" class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Welcome</h2>
      <p>
        shenas connects to the services people already use -- Garmin, Strava,
        Spotify, Lunch Money, Google Calendar -- and syncs the data into a
        local database. Transforms normalize it into canonical metrics.
        Dashboards visualize it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Everything is a plugin. If there's a data source you care about,
        you can write a connector in an afternoon. If there's a way to
        visualize it, you can build a dashboard in a weekend.
      </p>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Source plugins</h3>
          <p>Connect a new API or local file to shenas. dlt handles the pipeline; you define the tables.</p>
          <a href="#source-plugin">Write one &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Transform plugins</h3>
          <p>SQL, geofence, geocode, regex -- or write your own transform type.</p>
          <a href="#other-plugins">Learn more &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Dashboard plugins</h3>
          <p>Lit web components that query Arrow IPC and render charts.</p>
          <a href="#other-plugins">Learn more &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Dataset plugins</h3>
          <p>Define canonical metric schemas that transforms write into.</p>
          <a href="#other-plugins">Learn more &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Source plugin tutorial -->
  <section id="source-plugin" class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Write a source plugin</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">
        A source plugin is a Python package that defines tables as dataclasses
        and extracts data from an API. dlt handles incremental loading and
        schema management. You focus on the API.
      </p>

      <div class="step">
        <span class="step-num">1</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Scaffold the package</h3>
          <pre><code>mkdir -p plugins/sources/myapi/shenas_sources/myapi
cd plugins/sources/myapi

# pyproject.toml
cat &gt; pyproject.toml &lt;&lt;'EOF'
[project]
name = "shenas-source-myapi"
dependencies = ["dlt[duckdb]>=1.24.0", "shenas-source-core"]

[project.entry-points."shenas.sources"]
myapi = "shenas_sources.myapi.source:MyApiSource"
EOF</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <span class="step-num">2</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Define your tables</h3>
          <pre><code>from shenas_sources.core.table import EventTable, Field
from typing import Annotated, Any, Iterator

class Activities(EventTable):
    class _Meta:
        name = "activities"
        display_name = "Activities"
        pk = ("id",)

    id: Annotated[str, Field(db_type="VARCHAR")] = ""
    name: Annotated[str, Field(db_type="VARCHAR")] = ""
    duration_s: Annotated[int, Field(db_type="INTEGER", unit="s")] = 0
    time_at: Annotated[str, Field(db_type="TIMESTAMP")] = ""

    @classmethod
    def extract(cls, client: Any, **ctx) -> Iterator[dict]:
        yield from client.get_activities()</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <span class="step-num">3</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Create the source class</h3>
          <pre><code>from shenas_sources.core.source import Source

class MyApiSource(Source):
    name = "myapi"
    display_name = "My API"
    primary_table = "activities"

    def build_client(self):
        return MyApiClient(self.get_config_value("api_key"))

    def resources(self, client):
        from .tables import TABLES
        return [t.to_resource(client) for t in TABLES]</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <span class="step-num">4</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Install and sync</h3>
          <pre><code>uv sync  # installs your plugin as a workspace member
shenasctl source myapi sync</code></pre>
          <p>Your data is now in a local DuckDB database, queryable from dashboards and transforms.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Other plugins -->
  <section id="other-plugins" class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Other plugin types</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">
        Sources are the most common, but shenas has several plugin kinds.
        Each follows the same pattern: a Python package with an entry point.
      </p>

      <div class="plugin-table">
        <div class="plugin-row">
          <strong>Dataset</strong>
          <span>Define canonical metric tables (daily HRV, transactions, events). Transforms write into these.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="plugin-row">
          <strong>Transform</strong>
          <span>SQL, geofence, geocode, regex extract, LLM categorize -- or write your own transform type.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="plugin-row">
          <strong>Dashboard</strong>
          <span>Lit web components that query via Arrow IPC. Charts, tables, timelines -- anything visual.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="plugin-row">
          <strong>Frontend</strong>
          <span>The UI shell itself is a plugin. Write your own or extend the default.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="plugin-row">
          <strong>Theme</strong>
          <span>CSS custom properties that style everything at once. Ship a .css file and a Python class.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="plugin-row">
          <strong>Analysis</strong>
          <span>Hypothesis-driven analysis modes. Define an operation vocabulary and recipe strategy.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Share -->
  <section id="share" class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Share your plugin</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">
        Plugins are standard Python wheels. Publish to PyPI and anyone can
        install with <code>shenasctl source add myapi</code>.
      </p>

      <div class="step">
        <span class="step-num">1</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Build the wheel</h3>
          <pre><code>cd plugins/sources/myapi
hatchling build</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <span class="step-num">2</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Publish to PyPI</h3>
          <pre><code>twine upload dist/shenas_source_myapi-*.whl</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <span class="step-num">3</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Users install it</h3>
          <pre><code>shenasctl source add myapi</code></pre>
          <p>
            The CLI verifies the Ed25519 signature (if you sign it), installs
            the wheel, and the plugin appears in the UI automatically.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="mt-2">Plugin certification</h3>
      <p>
        Plugins that meet our quality bar -- tests, documentation, no
        credential leaks, clean table schemas -- can apply for
        <strong>certified</strong> status. Certified plugins get a badge
        in the UI and are listed in the official plugin directory.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="https://github.com/shenas-org/shenas/issues/new?template=plugin-certification.md">Apply for certification &rarr;</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="footer-links">
        <a href="https://shenas.net">shenas.net</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/shenas-org/shenas">GitHub</a>
        <a href="https://discord.gg/mY74eRU7MV">Discord</a>
        <a href="https://shenas.discourse.group/">Forum</a>
      </div>
      <p class="footer-copy">shenas is open source under the MIT license.</p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Base>

<style>
  /* Nav */
  nav {
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 100;
    background: rgba(253, 252, 250, 0.92);
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  .nav-inner {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0.8rem 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }
  .nav-logo {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .nav-org { color: var(--color-accent); }
  .nav-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .nav-links a { color: var(--color-text-muted); }
  .nav-links a:hover { color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: none; }

  /* Hero */
  .hero {
    padding: 6rem 0 4rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .accent { color: var(--color-accent); }
  .hero-sub {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }
  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  /* Sections */
  .section {
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }
  .section-alt {
    background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
  }
  .section h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .section-intro {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    max-width: 700px;
  }

  /* Cards */
  .card-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  .card {
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .card p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* Steps */
  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .step-num {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 2.2rem;
    height: 2.2rem;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-top: 0.2rem;
  }
  .step h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  /* Code */
  pre {
    background: #2c2c28;
    color: #e8e5df;
    padding: 1rem 1.2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
  }
  code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }
  p code {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.9em;
  }

  /* Plugin table */
  .plugin-table {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  .plugin-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    align-items: baseline;
  }
  .plugin-row strong {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 120px;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }
  .plugin-row span {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  /* Footer */
  footer {
    padding: 3rem 0;
    text-align: center;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  .footer-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .footer-copy {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .mt-2 { margin-top: 2rem; }
</style>
